 gravitational parameter GM which are one one order of magnitude\nsmaller than 10^-12 yr^-1. Dark Matter accretion on planets has, instead, less\nrelevant consequences for their satellites. Indeed, 4.5 Gyr ago their orbits\nwould have been just 10^-2-10^1 km wider than now. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Jan 2010 16:57:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 14 Jan 2010 17:36:42 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 17 Jan 2010 14:44:25 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 23 Jan 2010 06:17:40 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 26 Apr 2010 08:35:04 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 5 May 2010 19:54:23 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Tue, 11 May 2010 12:47:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-07-31"}
